# Video Production — REQUIRED reading

**Before writing any video code, any Remotion composition, any Listing.tsx rewrite, any video synth or render: read these two files.** This is non-negotiable.

## The two files

1. **`video_production_skills/VIDEO_PRODUCTION_SKILL.md`** — the master skill. Hard constraints, creative direction, render pipeline, AI video tier guide, brand rules, common-failure fixes, full Schoolhouse v5 lesson log.

2. **`video_production_skills/VIRAL_VIDEO_CONSTRAINTS.md`** — 30-second quick-reference card. Hard constraints as a pre-render and post-render checklist.

## The non-negotiables (summary — full detail in the skill file)

- **Length:** 30-45s target, never over 60s.
- **Hook:** motion engaged by frame 12 (0.4s), address text by 1s, VO content by 2s. No logo, no title card on black.
- **Cuts:** 2-3s standard, 4s max. 12+ photo beats in a 45s video.
- **Re-hooks at 25% and 50%, reveal in final 15%.**
- **Text safe zone:** 900×1400 inside 1080×1920. Body 48 px+, headline 64-80 px.
- **No brand elements in the video frame** (no logo, no "Ryan Realty," no phone, no agent name, no "REPRESENTED BY"). Brokerage attribution lives in the IG caption + bio.
- **Gimbal/parallax motion on every photo beat.** No static photos.
- **Three movement types per video minimum.**
- **Banned words:** stunning, nestled, boasts, gorgeous, breathtaking, must-see, "welcome to your dream home." No em-dashes, no hyphens in prose.
- **All numbers carry units.** "$3,025,000" not "3,025,000."
- **AI photo-to-video is OFF for interiors.** Reserved for aerials and exterior depth shots only, with strict slop checks.

## The render hygiene rules

- Remotion only. No Playwright video, no PIL composition.
- 1080×1920 portrait, 30 fps minimum.
- `concurrency=1` in render command.
- PhotoBeat parent div is `transparent` (so previous Sequence shows through fade-in).
- Default `crossfadeOut: 0` and Sequence overlap by 0.5s (so AbsoluteFill background never exposed).
- After render: `ffmpeg blackdetect d=0.03:pix_th=0.05` returns ZERO black sequences.
- Compress to under 100 MB with `-crf 24 -preset medium -movflags +faststart` before delivery.

## The quality gate

Before pushing or emailing, every item in `VIRAL_VIDEO_CONSTRAINTS.md` post-render checklist must be green. Self-enforce — don't wait for Matt to find an obvious bug.

## Common failures + fixes

The skill file has a full troubleshooting section. The greatest hits:

- **Black bars at transitions** → parent div transparent + crossfadeOut 0 + Sequence overlap (`PhotoBeat.tsx`).
- **Audio mismatch** → `previous_text` chained synth (`scripts/synth_vo_*.py`).
- **Deschutes pronunciation** → IPA `<phoneme>` tag on `eleven_v3` model.
- **Missing assets at render time** → run `build_v5_library.py` + verify symlinks BEFORE render, not after.
- **Generic feel** → re-read Section 2 (Creative direction) before scaffolding BEATS array.

## Schoolhouse v5 lesson log

The v1 → v5.9 sequence is the case study. Each major rule in the skill file is anchored to a specific round where the failure shipped. Reading the change log of `feat(listing-video-v5):` commits is the fastest way to internalize WHY each rule exists.

Most important inflection: **v5.7 (133s cinematic short film) → v5.8 (45s viral cut)**. A brokerage-credibility cinematic piece and a viral Reel are different products with different rules. Don't conflate them.
